<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>New South Wales have recorded an addition 17 new cases overnight as the CBD cluster grows to 49.</p>

<p>The state's Chief Health Officer Dr Kerry Chant announced the new cases during a press conference on Wednesday.</p>

<p>She said it is expected the CBD cluster would grow, as many attend the city every day, but it is important people are vigilant.</p>

<p>Dr Chant said it is important people come forward and check health websites for locations where COVID-19 cases have attended. </p>

<p>More to come. </p>
